Uses of Package
lombok.experimental

  • Packages that use lombok.experimental 
    Package Description
    lombok.core.handlers
    This package contains utility methods and classes shared between javac-specific feature implementations and eclipse-specific feature implementations.
    lombok.eclipse.handlers
    Contains the classes that implement the transformations for all of lombok's various features on the eclipse platform.
    lombok.javac.handlers
    Contains the classes that implement the transformations for all of lombok's various features on the javac v1.6 platform.
  • Classes in lombok.experimental used by lombok.core.handlers 
    Class and Description
    Accessors
    A container for settings for the generation of getters and setters.
  • Classes in lombok.experimental used by lombok.eclipse.handlers 
    Class and Description
    Accessors
    A container for settings for the generation of getters and setters.
  • Classes in lombok.experimental used by lombok.javac.handlers 
    Class and Description
    Accessors
    A container for settings for the generation of getters and setters.
    Delegate
    Put on any field to make lombok generate delegate methods that forward the call to this field.
    ExtensionMethod
    Extension methods enable you to "add" methods to existing types without creating a new derived type, recompiling, or otherwise modifying the original type.
    Helper
    Use on a method local class to indicate that all methods inside should be exposed to the rest of the method as if they were helper methods.
    UtilityClass
    An annotation to create utility classes.
    Visitable
    Makes a class a leaf of a visitor design pattern hierarchy.
    VisitableRoot
    Makes a class or interface the root of a visitor design pattern hierarchy.
    Wither
    Put on any field to make lombok build a 'wither' - a withX method which produces a clone of this object (except for 1 field which gets a new value).
